cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CV 

The paper discusses network steganography, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the manipulation of network transport domain, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also mentions multimedia embedding techniques, which are related to multimedia processing (cs.MM) and image processing (cs.CV). Finally, the paper introduces a new methodology for real-time network data steganography, which involves the use of system-level implementation and can be related to information theory (cs.IT).
